title: Kate Middleton wears stunning red gown for her first state banquet
text:
— katemiddletons.com (@katemiddletonss) October 20, 2015 
The royal mother-of-two also wore the sparkling tiara in December 2013 at a reception for diplomats at Buckingham Palace. 
Elizabeth Emanuel, a co-designer of Princess Diana’s wedding dress, has given her opinion on the choice made by Duchess Kate regarding the color of the dress. 
“Red is very important as a statement in itself as it matches the color of the Chinese flag and it means good fortune,” Emanuel said, according to People . 
Kate also accessorized her Jenny Packham red gown with diamond drop earrings and two bracelets. Spread the rumor
